<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF95FF84B68BFF7BA502FEF2" blockId="3.[174,1232,175,330]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
Diagnosis. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF95FF84B4CEFF64A751FF11" authorityName="Walkley" authorityYear="1960" box="[678,804,175,201]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Delomerista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF95FF84B4CEFF64A751FF11" box="[678,804,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">D. borealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has shorter malar space (about 0.25 × length of basal width of mandible), yellow upper hind corner of pronotum and tegulae, and shorter ovipositor (about 1.5–1.6 × length of hind tibia). Male has yellow tegulae (
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF95FF84B778FEDBA53EFEF2" box="[272,331,271,298]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[170,203,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[305,1093,562,1688]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[305,1093,558,1689]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig.1.Delomerista spp.1–2 —habitus,lateralview:1—D.cf.japonica, female;2 — D.novita,male;3 —D. novita, female, dorsal view of propodeum; 4, 5 — dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite: 4 — D. pfankuchi, male; 5 — D. novita, female; 6–10 — lateral view of ovipositor tip: 6 — D. pfankuchi; 7 — D. borealis; 8 — D. mandibularis; 9 — D.cf. japonica; 10 — D.japonica (non-Carpathian material); 11–12 — lateral view of two basal antennal segments: 11 — D. borealis; 12 — D. mandibularis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454726/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF95FF84B730FEDBA513FEF1" box="[344,358,271,297]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-372@4.[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Perithous spp.: 1 — P. speculator, female, habitus, lateral view; 2 — P. scurra, female, dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite; 3–4 — dorsal view of propodeum and metasomal tergites I–II, female: 3 — P. divinator; 4 — P. septemcinctorius; 5 — P. scurra, male, habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF95FF84B730FEDBA513FEF1" box="[344,358,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
